  <summary date="2019-01-03T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Universal Right to Vote by Mail Act of 2019 

 This bill prohibits a state from imposing additional conditions or requirements on the eligibility of an individual to cast a vote in federal elections by mail, except to the extent that it imposes a deadline for requesting the ballot and returning it to the appropriate state or local election official.</summary>
